OL,3,CMost parents regret giving children a
OL,4,Csmartphone - is it time for a ban?
OL,6,FHowever, a new survey of parents
OL,7,Faround the world, by phone
OL,8,Fmanufacturer Human Mobile Devices
OL,9,F(HMD), has suggested "solutions are
OL,10,Furgently needed" on young people's
OL,11,Fsmartphone usage.
OL,13,FThe research found that 11 is the
OL,14,Faverage age parents give their
OL,15,Fchildren smartphones, but 54% wish
OL,16,Fthey'd waited longer and a third said
OL,17,Fthe reason was because of the way
OL,18,Ftheir child's personality has changed
OL,19,Ffor the worse.
